PART 1Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî CREATE RESOURCE CONTROLLER
1Ô∏è‚É£ Create Model + Migration + Resource Controller
php artisan make:model Product -mcr

üìÑ Files Created
app/Models/Product.php
app/Http/Controllers/ProductController.php
database/migrations/xxxx_create_products_table.php

2Ô∏è‚É£ Migration Example

üìÑ database/migrations/*_create_products_table.php

Schema::create('products', function (Blueprint $table) {
    $table->id();
    $table->string('name');
    $table->decimal('price', 8, 2);
    $table->timestamps();
});

php artisan migrate

PART 2Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî DEFINE RESOURCE ROUTES (IMPORTANT üî•)

üìÑ routes/web.php

use App\Http\Controllers\ProductController;

Route::resource('products', ProductController::class);

üîπ Resource Routes Mapping
HTTP	URL	Controller Method	Purpose
GET	/products	index	List all records
GET	/products/create	create	Show create form
POST	/products	store	Save new record
GET	/products/{product}	show	Show single record
GET	/products/{product}/edit	edit	Show edit form
PUT/PATCH	/products/{product}	update	Update record
DELETE	/products/{product}	destroy	Delete record
PART 3Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî RESOURCE CONTROLLER METHODS

üìÑ app/Http/Controllers/ProductController.php

<?php

namespace App\Http\Controllers;

use App\Models\Product;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;

class ProductController extends Controller
{
    // 1Ô∏è‚É£ List all products
    public function index()
    {
        $products = Product::all();
        return view('products.index', compact('products'));
    }

    // 2Ô∏è‚É£ Show create form
    public function create()
    {
        return view('products.create');
    }

    // 3Ô∏è‚É£ Store new product
    public function store(Request $request)
    {
        Product::create($request->all());
        return redirect()->route('products.index');
    }

    // 4Ô∏è‚É£ Show single product
    public function show(Product $product)
    {
        return view('products.show', compact('product'));
    }

    // 5Ô∏è‚É£ Show edit form
    public function edit(Product $product)
    {
        return view('products.edit', compact('product'));
    }

    // 6Ô∏è‚É£ Update product
    public function update(Request $request, Product $product)
    {
        $product->update($request->all());
        return redirect()->route('products.index');
    }

    // 7Ô∏è‚É£ Delete product
    public function destroy(Product $product)
    {
        $product->delete();
        return redirect()->route('products.index');
    }
}

PART 4Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî MODEL CONFIGURATION (IMPORTANT)

üìÑ app/Models/Product.php

<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model;

class Product extends Model
{
    protected $fillable = ['name', 'price'];
}

